'''Heikki Nurmio''' (1887-1947) - [[Finnish Jäger troops|Finnish jäger]] and writer. He is remembered for writing the lyrics for "Jääkärien marssi" (''[[Jäger March]]'') composed by [[Jean Sibelius]] in 1917.

Heikki Nurmio joined the Finnish jägers ([[27th Jäger Battalion (Finland)|27th Jäger Battalion]]) in 1916 in Germany. He participated in combats in Germany's Eastern front and fought against [[Russian empire]] in the Civil War. His book "Jääkärin päiväkirja" (Diary of a jäger) was published in 1918 and he became known also as the author of war novels that were meant for younger audiences.


