'''Michel Étienne Descourtilz''' (25 November 1777, Boiste near [[Pithiviers]] – 1835, [[Paris]]), was a French physician, [[botanist]] and [[historiographer]] of the [[Haitian Revolution]]. He was the father of illustrator [[Jean-Théodore Descourtilz]], with whom he sometimes collaborated.<ref>[http://data.bnf.fr/12601563/jean_theodore_descourtilz/ Jean Théodore Descourtilz] data.BnF.fr</ref>
In 1799, after completing his medical studies he traveled to [[Charleston, South Carolina]] and [[Santiago de Cuba|Santiago, Cuba]], arriving in Haiti on 2 April.<ref name=IU>[https://books.google.com/books?id=O-nwqydcvtQC&pg=PA36&lpg=PA36&dq=Descourtilz+Charleston+Haiti&source=bl&ots=yp5Ea9S7mh&sig=3KO8r_dj9OnADAcdxESn5TNLIcM&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwix94-luvDJAhVJNT4KHWFKA5Y4ChDoAQg9MAg#v=onepage&q=Descourtilz%20Charleston%20Haiti&f=false Symb. antill] by [[Ignatz Urban]]</ref> Despite a passport from [[Toussaint Louverture]] and serving as physician with the forces of [[Jean-Jacques Dessalines]], he was in constant danger.<ref>[http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k31234p.zoom.r=Descourtilz.f292.langEN.pagination BnF.Gallica] (biography in French)</ref> His plant collections were mostly from between [[Port-au-Prince]] and [[Cap-Haïtien]] and along the [[Artibonite River]].<ref name=IU/> All his natural history collections and many drawings were destroyed during the course of the revolution.{{Citation needed|date=December 2015}} In 1803 he returned to France, worked as a physician in a hospital at [[Beaumont-sur-Oise|Beaumont]] and served as president of the Paris [[Linnean Society]].<ref name=IU/>
As a [[taxonomy (biology)|taxonomist]] he circumscribed the genus ''Nauchea'' (family [[Fabaceae]]).<ref>[http://www.tropicos.org/Name/40025446 Nauchea Descourt.] Tropicos</ref>
==Bibliography== *[https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/bibliography/4351 ''Flore pittoresque et médicale des Antilles, ou, Histoire naturelle des plantes usuelles des colonies françaises, anglaises, espagnoles et portugaises; par M.E. Descourtilz. Peinte par J. Th. Descourtilz. Vols. 1-8''] *[https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/bibliography/49377 ''Voyages d'un naturaliste, et ses observations faites sur les trois règnes de la nature, dans plusieurs ports de mer français, en Espagne, au continent de l'Amérique Septentrionale, à Saint Yago de Cub. Vols.1-3''] * [http://www.worldcat.org/search?q=descourtilz&fq=ap%3A%22descourtilz%2C+m+e%22&qt=facet_ap%3A Complete bibliography on WorldCat.] {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2011}} {{botanist|Descourt.|Descourtilz, Michel Étienne}}
