{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}} {{Use Australian English|date=October 2016}} {{Infobox person |name = Phillip Bradley |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_name = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1955|05|18}} |birth_place = Sydney |death_date = |death_place = |nationality = [[Australian]] |known_for = Military historian |occupation = |footnotes = }}
'''Phillip Bradley''' (born 18 May 1955) is an Australian military historian who has written five books as well as numerous articles for ''Wartime'' and ''[[After the Battle]]'' magazine. He has been described as "One of the finest chroniclers of the Australian Army's role in the New Guinea campaign".<ref>[http://www.theaustralian.news.com.au/story/0,25197,23599038-31477,00.html The Australian: The Digger Distilled] (Retrieved 23 May 2009).</ref>
Bradley has travelled many Australian battlefields, including sites in [[Papua New Guinea]], [[Turkey]] and [[France]].
