{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
In geology a '''succession''' is series of [[stratum|strata]] or rock units in [[chronology|chronological]] order. Rock successions can be seen in cross-sections through rock, for example in a road cutting or cliff. With sedimentary layers of rocks, newer units will be above older units. 

