'''Wendy R. Childs''' (born March 1943) is [[emeritus professor]] of later [[medieval history]] at the [[University of Leeds]]. She is a specialist in the [[economic history]] of [[medieval Europe]] and the [[international trade]] of England in the 13th and 14th centuries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leeds.ac.uk/arts/profile/20041/122/wendy_childs|title=Profile - Faculty of Arts, Humanities and Cultures - University of Leeds - Wendy Childs|first=University of|last=Leeds|website=www.leeds.ac.uk|accessdate=3 December 2017}}</ref>
